Qualified professionals from the Luhya community should be allowed to freely work in the Rift Valley, a Western Kenya caucus has said.The Western Caucus for Change criticised the MPs and two governors from the Kalenjin community for opposing Prof Laban Ayiro s appointment as Moi University acting vice chancellor. This is not the first time we are being harassed, we witnessed Prof Teresa Akenga s appointment as VC of Eldoret University rejected, interim chairman Geoffrey Njuya told the Star on the phone on Sunday. He said professionals should be able to work anywhere in the country.